# Testing Rules

References:

- docs/coding-standards.md
- docs/tech-architecture.md
- docs/user-flows.md

---

# Testing Philosophy

Goal:

Protect business-critical functionality.

Focus on:

- Business logic
- Financial logic
- Integrations

Do not chase arbitrary coverage percentages.

---

# Testing Priorities

Priority 1

Financial Logic

Examples:

- Cashback calculation
- Commission processing
- Withdrawal validation

Priority 2

Business Logic

Examples:

- Affiliate link generation
- Order processing
- Dashboard calculations

Priority 3

Infrastructure

Examples:

- Accesstrade integration
- Webhook processing

Priority 4

UI

Only critical UI flows.

---

# Test Project Structure

Backend

```text
backend/tests/

├── Cashback.UnitTests
└── Cashback.IntegrationTests
```

---

Unit Tests

```text
Application/
Domain/
Shared/
```

---

Integration Tests

```text
Api/
Database/
Webhooks/
```

---

# Unit Test Rules

Unit tests must:

- Be fast
- Be isolated
- Avoid external services

Mock:

- Repositories
- External APIs
- OAuth Providers

Never call real services in unit tests.

---

# Naming Convention

Pattern:

```text
MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult
```

Examples:

```text
CreateWithdrawal_InsufficientBalance_ReturnsFailure

GenerateAffiliateLink_ValidRequest_ReturnsLink

ApproveWithdrawal_ValidRequest_UpdatesBalance
```

---

# Business Logic Coverage

Must Test

Cashback

- Calculate cashback
- Commission distribution

Withdrawals

- Balance validation
- Minimum amount validation
- Status transitions

Orders

- Creation
- Approval
- Cancellation

Webhooks

- Duplicate protection
- Signature validation

---

# Handler Tests

Every critical command handler should be testable.

Examples:

```text
GenerateAffiliateLinkHandler

CreateWithdrawalHandler

ApproveWithdrawalHandler

ProcessAccesstradeWebhookHandler
```

---

# Validation Tests

Validators should be tested.

Examples:

```text
CreateWithdrawalValidator

GenerateAffiliateLinkValidator
```

Must verify:

- Required fields
- Invalid values
- Boundary conditions

---

# Domain Tests

Domain entities should test:

- State changes
- Business rules
- Financial calculations

Examples:

```text
UserBalanceTests

OrderStatusTests

WithdrawalRulesTests
```

---

# Integration Test Rules

Integration tests verify:

- API endpoints
- Database interactions
- Webhook processing

Use test database.

Never use production database.

---

# API Tests

Critical endpoints must be tested.

Examples:

```text
POST /affiliate-links

POST /withdrawals

GET /dashboard

POST /webhooks/accesstrade
```

Verify:

- Status codes
- Response structure
- Authorization

---

# Webhook Tests

Must test:

- Valid payload
- Invalid signature
- Duplicate event
- Retry event

Webhook processing must be idempotent.

---

# Database Tests

Verify:

- Migrations
- Constraints
- Relationships

Critical financial operations must be validated.

---

# Mocking Rules

Allowed:

- Moq
- NSubstitute

Prefer:

Moq

---

Mock:

- IOrderRepository
- IUserRepository
- IAccesstradeClient

Do not mock:

- Pure business logic

---

# Frontend Testing Rules

Focus on:

- Forms
- Authentication flows
- Critical user journeys

Examples:

- Login flow
- Generate affiliate link
- Create withdrawal request

---

# What Not To Test

Avoid testing:

- Framework internals
- EF Core implementation details
- Simple DTOs
- Auto-generated code

---

# Financial Safety Tests

Mandatory

Withdrawal

✓ Insufficient balance

✓ Negative amount

✓ Zero amount

✓ Successful request

---

Commission

✓ Approved commission

✓ Rejected commission

✓ Duplicate webhook

---

# Regression Tests

When fixing a bug:

Create a test reproducing the bug first.

Then fix the bug.

---

# Code Generation Checklist

✓ Unit tests created for business logic

✓ Integration tests for critical APIs

✓ Validation tests exist

✓ Financial logic tested

✓ External services mocked

✓ No real external calls

✓ Clear naming convention

✓ Idempotency verified for webhooks
